main event: A civilian in San Angelo, Texas reported seeing a bright white round light moving northward on August 5, 1968.
interesting points: The observer was requested to complete an AF Form 117 to provide more information, but did not return it within 30 days.
The Air Force's Aerial Phenomena Office, led by Lt. Colonel Hector Quintanilla, sent a letter requesting the observer to complete the AF Form 117 for further investigation.
The report indicates that the sighting was made at 2230Z (6:30 PM local time) and the object was described as being the size of a dollar bill.
Multiple witnesses in the San Angelo, Texas area reported similar sightings, including a mechanic, an oil field worker, and a housewife, all of whom were deemed reliable observers.
The weather conditions at the time of the sighting were provided, including surface winds of 9 knots and winds aloft of 22 knots.
